laboratory_examinations.findings: 6 mm hypodensity in the left hepatic lobe is too small to accurately characterize, statistically most likely a cyst, hemangioma, or biliary hamartoma. The appendix is dilated with wall hyperemia and moderate surrounding fat stranding in the right lower quadrant. Wall edema and/or phlegmon at the base of the appendix observed. No evidence of a drainable fluid collection or free air. Minimal secondary inflammatory changes in the cecum related to appendicitis.
MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA ( >= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.
